        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "test: make zalo credentials tests compatible with Windows",
        "body": "Enables running Zalo credentials tests on Windows: 1) by conditionalizing POSIX-specific permission stat mode checks so we only assert them on POSIX platforms, while validating directory/file presence on Windows, and 2) by replacing the hardcoded Windows skip with a dynamic file symlink capability probe.\n\n### Verified Windows Proof\n\nThe following test execution log shows the test run on Windows. All 7 runnable tests passed successfully, and the symlink test was gracefully skipped (1 skipped, 7 passed) due to the absence of symlink privileges:\n\n```\n RUN  v4.1.7 C:/Users/ANIRUDDHA/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/openclaw\n\n ✓  extension-zalo  ../../extensions/zalouser/src/zalo-js.credentials.test.ts (8 tests | 1 skipped) 443ms\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  7 passed | 1 skipped (8)\n```\n",
